      "x`, so we have:\n`(x : ℝ≥0∞)⁻¹ = (x⁻¹ : ℝ≥0∞)` if `x ≠ 0`, and `(0 : NNReal) : ℝ≥0∞ = 0` and `(0 : ℝ≥0∞)⁻¹ = ⊤`, but `((1 : ℕR) : ℝ≥0∞)⁻¹ = 1⁻¹ : ℝ≥0∞ = 1`, etc.\n\nBut for `x : NNReal`, `(x : ℝ≥0∞) = (x : ℝ≥0∞)` and `(x : ℝ≥0∞)⁻¹ = ((x⁻¹ : NNReal) : ℝ≥0∞)` if `x ≠ 0`. \n\nBut in Lean, `(x : ℝ≥0∞)⁻¹` is defined as:\n- `0` if `x = ⊤`\n- `⊤` if `x = 0`\n- `x⁻¹` otherwise (but this is not quite true; see Lean's definition).\n\nBut actually, for `x : ℝ≥0∞`, `x⁻¹` is defined as:\nif `x = 0`, then `⊤`\nif `x = ⊤`, then `0`\notherwise `x⁻¹ : ℝ≥0` (where `x` is finite, but here `x : ℝ≥0∞` includes `⊤`).\n\nBut in our case, `∑ i ∈ s, (p i)⁻¹ : NNReal`, and `p i : NNReal`, and since `p i ≠ 0`, `(p i)⁻¹ : NNReal`, and thus `∑ i ∈ s, (p i)⁻¹ : NNReal` is `≥ 0`. \n\nBut `(∑ i ∈ s, (p i)⁻¹ : NNReal) : ℝ≥0∞` is the same as the sum in `ℝ≥0∞`.\n\nThus, if `(∑ i ∈ s, (p i)⁻¹ : NNReal) : ℝ≥0∞ = ⊤`, then `(∑ i ∈ s, (p i)⁻¹ : NNReal) = ⊤` in `NNReal`, but this cannot happen unless `s` is infinite, which it isn't (`s : Finset ι`).\n\nWait no, no no no no no, `Finset.sum` is still finite, and `(p i)⁻¹ : NNReal` is finite, so `∑ i ∈ s, (p i)⁻¹ : NNReal` is finite. \n\nTherefore, `(∑ i ∈ s, (p i)⁻¹ : NNReal) : ℝ≥0∞ = (∑ i ∈ s, (p i)⁻¹ : ℝ≥0)` (the coercion to `ℝ≥0∞` takes it directly to the `ℝ≥0` part).\n\nSimilarly, `(p i)⁻¹ : NNReal`, and `(p i : ℝ≥0∞) = (p i : NNReal)`.\n\nBut the problem is that `(∑ x ∈ s, (↑(p x))⁻¹ : ℝ≥0∞)` is `(∑ x ∈ s, (p x : ℝ≥0∞)⁻¹ : ℝ≥0∞)` and since `(p x : ℝ≥0∞)⁻¹ = ((p x : NNReal)⁻¹ : ℝ≥0)` because `p x : NNReal` is finite and non-zero.\n\nThus, `(∑ x ∈ s, (↑(p x))⁻¹ : ℝ≥0∞)` is `(∑ x ∈ s, (p x : NNReal)⁻¹ : NNReal : ℝ≥0)` because the sum is in `NNReal` and then coerced to `ℝ≥0∞`.\n\nBut in Lean, `(↑(∑ i ∈ s, (p i)⁻¹) : ℝ≥0∞)` is `(∑ i ∈ s, (p i : NNReal)⁻¹ : NNReal : ℝ≥0∞)`.\n\nSimilarly, `(∑ x ∈ s, (↑(p x))⁻¹ : ℝ≥0∞)` is `((∑ x ∈ s, (p x : NNReal)⁻¹ : NNReal) : ℝ≥0∞)`.\n\nSo the difference between `(∑ x ∈ s, (↑(p x))⁻¹ : ℝ≥0∞)` and `(∑ i ∈ s, (p i)⁻¹ : NNReal : ℝ≥0∞)` is just coercions.\n\nIn Lean:\n\n`(∑ x ∈ s, (↑(p x))⁻¹ : ℝ≥0∞)` is `(∑ x ∈ s, (p x : ℝ≥0∞)⁻¹ : ℝ≥0∞)`, and `(p x : ℝ≥0∞)⁻¹ = ((p x : NNReal)⁻¹ : ℝ≥0∞)`.\n\nSimilarly, `(↑(∑ i ∈ s, (p i)⁻¹)) : ℝ≥0∞` is `(∑ i ∈ s, (p i : NNReal)⁻¹ : NNReal : ℝ≥0∞)`.\n\nBut because `(∑ x ∈ s, (p x : NNReal)⁻¹ : NNReal) = (∑ x ∈ s, (p x : NNReal)⁻¹ : NNReal)`, then after coercing to `ℝ≥0∞`, they are equal.\n\nTherefore:\n`(∑ x ∈ s, (↑(p x))⁻¹ : ℝ≥0∞) = (↑(∑ i ∈ s, (p i)⁻¹) : ℝ≥0∞)`.\n\nThen, `(∑ x ∈ s, (↑(p x))⁻¹ : ℝ≥0∞)⁻¹⁻¹ = (↑(∑ i ∈ s, (p i)⁻¹) : ℝ≥0∞)⁻¹⁻¹`.\n\nBut `(↑(∑ i ∈ s, (p i)⁻¹) : ℝ≥0∞)⁻¹⁻¹ = (↑(∑ i ∈ s, (p i)⁻¹) : ℝ≥0∞)` because `((∑ i ∈ s, (p i)⁻¹ : NNReal)) : ℝ≥0∞` is not `0` or `⊤`.\n\nThus, the hypothesis becomes:\n`(p i)⁻¹ + (∑ x ∈ s, (↑(p x))⁻¹ : ℝ≥0∞)⁻¹⁻¹ = (p i)⁻¹ + (∑ i ∈ s, (p i)⁻¹ : NNReal : ℝ≥0∞)`.\n\nBut then we need to prove that `(p i)⁻¹ + (∑ i ∈ s, (p i)⁻¹ : NNReal : ℝ≥0∞) = q⁻¹`.\n\nBut in the goal, it's `(p i)⁻¹ + ((∑ i ∈ s, (p i)⁻¹ : NNReal : ℝ≥0∞)⁻¹ : ℝ≥0∞)⁻¹`.\n\nWhich is `(p i)⁻¹ + ( (∑ i ∈ s, (p i)⁻¹ : NNReal : ℝ≥0∞)⁻¹ )⁻¹ = (p i)⁻¹ + (∑ i ∈ s, (p i)⁻¹ : NNReal : ℝ≥0∞)`, because",
      "th",
      "by\n    have h₁ : (p i : ℝ≥0∞) ≠ 0 := by\n      norm_cast\n      exact hp i\n    have h₂ : (∑ i ∈ s, (p i : ℝ≥0∞)⁻¹ : ℝ≥0∞) ≠ 0 := by\n      simp_all [hp, NNReal.ne_zero]\n      <;> positivity\n    have h₃ : (q : ℝ≥0∞) ≠ 0 := by\n      have h₄ : (q : ℝ≥0∞) = (∑ i ∈ s, (p i : ℝ≥0∞)⁻¹ : ℝ≥0∞)⁻¹ := by\n        simp_all [ENNReal.ext_iff, hp]\n        <;> norm_num at *\n        <;> ring_nf at *\n        <;> simp_all [ENNReal.ext_iff, hp]\n        <;> norm_num at *\n        <;> linarith\n      rw [h₄]\n      positivity\n    simp_all [ENNReal.HolderTriple, hp]\n    <;>\n    (try\n      simp_all [ENNReal.ext_iff, hp]\n      <;>\n      norm_num at *\n      <;>\n      ring_nf at *\n      <;>\n      simp_all [ENNReal.ext_iff, hp]\n      <;>\n      norm_num at *\n      <;>\n      linarith)\n    <;>\n    (try\n      simp_all [ENNReal.sum_le_sum]\n      <;>\n      norm_num at *\n      <;>\n      ring_nf at *\n      <;>\n      simp_all [ENNReal.ext_iff, hp]\n      <;>\n      norm_num at *\n      <;>\n      linarith)\n    <;>\n    (try positivity)\n  ",
